# Swift Conventions

## Watch App (`apps/watch-ios/TrackBallWatch Watch App/`)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `InputCaptureView.swift` | Full-screen `SpatialEventGesture` touch capture |
| `GestureRecognizer.swift` | On-device gesture classification (tap/fling/swipe) |
| `WatchSessionManager.swift` | `WCSession.sendMessage()` dispatch to iPhone |
| `CrownHandler.swift` | Digital Crown → CROWN packets |
| `TBPPacket.swift` | Little-endian packet serializer matching `tbp_spec.md` |
| `ExtendedRuntimeManager.swift` | `WKExtendedRuntimeSession` to keep app alive |

## Companion App (`apps/companion-ios/TrackBallCompanion/`)

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `WatchRelayService.swift` | WCSession receiver → UDP bridge |
| `UDPRelay.swift` | NWConnection UDP client to desktop |
| `PairingService.swift` | QR code scanning → DesktopConfig storage |
| `BonjourBrowser.swift` | mDNS `_tbp._udp.local` discovery |
| `MainView.swift` | SwiftUI main screen |
| `AppDelegate.swift` | PushKit VoIP background wakeup |

## Rules

- Minimum targets: iOS **17.0** (watch-ios project), iOS **16.0** (companion-ios), watchOS **11.0**
- SwiftUI for all UI; no UIKit unless framework requires it
- Packet serialization must match `shared/protocol/tbp_spec.md` exactly (little-endian, fixed sizes)
- Touch coordinates: normalize `CGPoint` to `-32767..32767` range
- Gesture recognition runs on-watch to minimize BT traffic
- Two Xcode projects exist: `apps/watch-ios/TrackBallWatch.xcodeproj` (unified watch+iOS) and `apps/companion-ios/TrackBallCompanion.xcodeproj` (standalone companion)
- Both projects have `project.yml` for XcodeGen; regenerate with `xcodegen` when targets change
- Build without signing: `CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY="-" CODE_SIGNING_REQUIRED=NO CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=NO`
